==English==

===Alternative forms===
* [[sow the wind and reap the whirlwind]]

===Etymology===
A reference to [[w:Book of Hosea|Hosea]] [[s:Bible (King James)/Hosea#Chapter 8|8:7]]: "they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind"

===Proverb===
{{head|en|proverb|head=[[sow|Sow]] [[the]] [[wind]], [[reap]] [[the]] [[whirlwind]]}}

# Every decision has consequences; a person's actions will come back to him.

====Synonyms====
* [[what goes around comes around]].
* [[get out what one puts in]].
* [[reap what one sows]].

